In the [Köppen climate system], these climates grade off toward [temperate climates](/Temperate_climate) equator‑ward where winters are less severe and [semi‑arid climates](/Semi‑arid_climate) or [arid climates](/Arid_climate) where precipitation becomes inadequate for tall‑grass [prairies](/Prairie) and shrublands. In Europe these climates may grade off into [oceanic climates](/Oceanic_climate) ( Cfb ) or [subpolar oceanic climates](/Subpolar_oceanic_climate) ( Cfc ) in which the influence of cool oceanic air masses is more marked toward the west. In western and eastern Asia, and the central United States these climates grade off toward [humid subtropical climates](/Humid_subtropical_climate) ( Cfa/Cwa ), [subtropical highland climates](/Subtropical_highland_climate) ( Cwb ), or [Mediterranean climates](/Mediterranean_climate) ( Csa/Csb ) to the south.

